ollowing{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/badlogic/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/badlogic/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/badlogic/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/badlogic/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/badlogic/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/badlogic/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/badlogic/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2014-03-18T00:15:12Z","updated_at":"2014-03-18T00:15:12Z","body":"GearJoint holding on to them is fine imo. Need to think about how this\naffects ownership of these joints as well as their lifecycle.\nOn Mar 18, 2014 12:03 AM, \"MobiDevelop\" notifications@github.com wrote:\n\n> @badlogic https://github.com/badlogic Does it make more sense for World\n> to expose getting a joint by its address (this is rather unsavory as it\n> would have to be public), or simply passing the constituent joints to the\n> GearJoint at construction time. Most of the wrapper favors, calling through\n> to the native side for everything (so you don't get stale data, I suppose),\n> however in this case the constituent joints cannot be modified (or can\n> they?), so maybe it makes sense just to let the GearJoint hold on to them\n> on the Java side. Thoughts?\n> \n> ## \n> \n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHubhttps://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/1173#issuecomment-37881870\n> .\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/37886948/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"badlogic","id":514052,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUxNDA1Mg==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/514052?v=4","gravatar_id